<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="110" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="110">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="110">Known only from a pair of females which are moderately darkly colored with three indistinct transverse maculae. The apex of the prosternal process is lanceolate. Given the absence of known males, a definitive diagnosis is difficult to establish.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
